*ngSwitchCase DIRECTIVE

- if we wanna compare the value of the field or property aginst multiple values 
    then we need to use ngSwitchCase.

            <ul class="nav nav-pills">
                <li class="nav-link" [class.active]="viewMode == 'map'">
                    <a (click)="viewMode = 'map'">Map View</a>
                </li>
                <li class="nav-link" [class.active]="viewMode == 'list'">
                    <a (click)="viewMode = 'list'">List View</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <div [ngSwitch]="viewMode">
                <div *ngSwitchCase="'map'">Map view content</div>     // 1)
                <div *ngSwitchCase="'list'">List view content</div>   // 2)
                <div *ngSwitchDefault>Otherwise</div>
            </div>

            -> here, depending upon the value(map or list) of property 'viewMode',
                we will be rendering the div element body.
                - if viewMode == 'map' then 1)
                - IF viewMode == 'list' then 2)
            -> if we click on a 'Map view' the value of property viewMode will be set to 'map'.
                similarly, if we click on a 'List view' the value of property viewMode will be 
                set to 'list'